findings.Liver: Homogenous attenuation throughout with diffuse hypodensity, compatible with hepatic steatosis; no focal lesions.
findings.Kidneys: Normal and symmetric size, normal nephrogram; no nephrolithiasis, ureterolithiasis, or hydronephrosis.
findings.Appendix: Dilated, measuring up to 13 mm with significant fat stranding at the tip; punctate calcification may represent an appendicolith.

Lymph Nodes.Lateral caval node: Increased in size (2.8 x 3.0 cm, previous 3.6 x 2.2 cm).
Lymph Nodes.Left upper quadrant node: Decreased in size (1.6 x 2.4 cm, previous 1.8 x 3.1 cm).
Lymph Nodes.Right lower quadrant node: Decreased in size (0.7 x 1.3 cm, previous 1.1 x 1.5 cm).

laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Lateral caval lymph node increased in size, while the left upper quadrant and right lower quadrant lymph nodes decreased in size.
